# Cursor Project Rules (Latest Version)

## Key Features & Changes
- Geocoding and map integration for any selected .json file
- OpenStreetMap visualization with popups for all found coordinates
- Missing locations listed below the map
- City and district/area are user inputs (default: Istanbul, Turkey), not hardcoded
- Gemini labeling always saves to labeled_output.json
- Modern, user-friendly Streamlit UI with real-time feedback
- No references to deleted files or non-existent features
- No sensitive or secret information in documentation

## Project Structure
- Main app: sbee_streamlit.py
- Geocoding CLI: geocoding_cli.py (auto-run from UI)
- ScrapingBee/ for scraping/cache logic
- Data files: output.json, changed.json, labeled_output.json, etc.
- API keys in .env (never in code)

## Coding & Documentation
- Use type hints, docstrings, and PEP 8
- Handle errors gracefully, always provide user feedback
- Keep README and rules up to date with actual features
- Never expose API keys or sensitive data

## Versioning Protocol
- When versioning, update README.md, README_rules.md (Turkish), and .cursorrules (English) to reflect all changes
- Commit and push to GitHub after versioning 